BENIN – The Edo Police Command has said it has arrested three suspects in connec­tion with mysterious death of a female trader who was allegedly attacked, robbed, gang raped and murdered on her way to the market on Evbuosa Road near Obozogbe in Orhiomwon Local Government Area of Edo State. The police in a report said three persons who are now in Police custo­dy in Edo State allegedly accosted the woman and robbed her of the sum of N30,000. Police investigation revealed that the three assailants then dragged the woman into a nearby bush where they took turns to rape and later left her with life-threatening injuries. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The yet to be identified woman who could not stand the serious bruises in­flicted on her later died in the bush. But some persons who were said to be working in a nearby farm heard the screaming of a woman but could not find her when they got to the scene, an indication that the suspects had re­located her far into the bush. Lagos To Arraign 60 For Allegedly Driving Against Traffic Gunmen Kill 5 Persons, Child In Benue However, a shirt be­longing to a member of the village was found at the scene of the crime. The owner of the shirt was later identified to be one Destiny Osa. He was then handed over to men of the Ugo Police Division who in turn handed him over to men of the Anti-Kid­napping and Cyber Crime Unit of the Edo State Police Command for discrete Investiga­tion. Using high technical intelligence, the said Destiny Osa alleged­ly told the police how they attacked, robbed, raped and murdered the wom­an in the bush by 7 a.m. He then took the police to arrest the other two members of the gang. Their names were given as Etim Zion and Samuel Jeremiah both from Akwa Ibom State but resident in the area. During the police investigation, the woman’s hair attachment and her cloth referred to as ”wrapper” were re­covered at the scene of the crime. The prime suspect, Destiny Osa, later led the police and another inves­tigative team to the bush area where the woman was gang-raped. The body has since been deposited in the mortuary for autopsy and fur­ther investigation. Contacted, Edo State Police Public Relations Officer, SP Chidi Nwabuzor, who confirmed the incident said, no one has come for the body of the fe­male trader. SP Nwabuzor advised anyone whose family member left home since Saturday, December 19, 2020 to Evbu­osa around Obozogbe in Orhiomwon Local Government Area of Edo State and has not returned home to contact the office of the Anti-Kidnapping/Cy­ber Crime Unit of the Edo State Police Command in Benin City. He assured that the three suspects would be diligently prosecuted at the end of investigations. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION